"title": "2330: Jesus Christ, as shepherd",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2330: jesus christ, as shepherd",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A title for Jesus Christ indicating believers' dependence on him as he protects, tends and guides those whom he knows intimately.</p>\n<h2>Prophecies about the shepherd Messiah</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:23\">EZK 34:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:24\">EZK 37:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:2\">MIC 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:6\">MAT 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:4\">MIC 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech13:7\">ZEC 13:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:31\">MAT 26:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:27\">MRK 14:27</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's role as the good shepherd</h2>\n<h3>He has compassion for the helpless</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:36\">MAT 9:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:34\">MRK 6:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:52\">JHN 11:52</a></p>\n<h3>He seeks lost sheep</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:12-Matt18:14\">MAT 18:12–18:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:3-Luke15:7\">LUK 15:3–15:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:6\">MAT 10:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:24\">MAT 15:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:10\">LUK 19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:16\">JHN 10:16</a></p>\n<h3>He knows his own sheep</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:14-John10:15\">JHN 10:14–10:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:32\">MAT 25:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:27\">JHN 10:27</a></p>\n<h3>His sheep know his voice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:4\">JHN 10:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:3\">JHN 10:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:5\">JHN 10:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:16\">JHN 10:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:27\">JHN 10:27</a></p>\n<h3>He provides for and protects his sheep</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:9\">JHN 10:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:28\">JHN 10:28</a></p>\n<h3>He lays down his life for his sheep</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11\">JHN 10:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:31\">MAT 26:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:27\">MRK 14:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:14-John10:15\">JHN 10:14–10:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:17-John10:18\">JHN 10:17–10:18</a></p>\n<h3>He judges the sheep</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:32-Matt25:46\">MAT 25:32–25:46</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ shepherds his flock</h2>\n<h3>Christians are Jesus Christ's flock</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:32\">LUK 12:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:16\">MAT 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:16\">JHN 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:29\">ACT 20:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:36\">ROM 8:36</a></p>\n<h3>Under-shepherds are appointed over Jesus Christ's flock</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:15-John21:17\">JHN 21:15–21:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2-1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:2–5:4</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ the risen Lord is Shepherd</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:17\">REV 7:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:20\">HEB 13:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:25\">1PE 2:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:4</a></p>",
